									<RECORD id="0-0-0-38937" number="49786" version="3">
										<HEADING>§ 21-988 Posting information regarding the process used in determining identified seat need.</HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-9809" name="21-988"/>§ 21-988 Posting information regarding the process used in determining identified seat need.</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38938" number="49787" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>a.<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Definitions.</CHARFORMAT> For the purposes of this section, the following terms have the following meanings: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38939" number="49788" version="1765">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Identified seat need.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;identified seat need&quot; means the number of seats required through the construction of new facilities to meet the enrollment needs in each community school district identified in the five-year educational facilities capital plan created by the department pursuant to section 2590-p of the education law. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38940" number="49789" version="1765">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Subdistrict.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;subdistrict&quot; means all geographic boundaries used by the department and the New York city school construction authority to identify where new capital funding will be targeted for building new schools as defined in section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="21-989" destination-id="0-0-0-9811">21-989</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38941" number="49790" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>b.<TAB tab-count="1"/>No later than December 1, 2019, and annually thereafter on or before December 1, the department shall, to the extent such information is accessible by the department, post conspicuously on its website a report, which shall include, but need not be limited to: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38942" number="49791" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>1.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The process and inputs used to determine identified seat need, including but not limited to: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38943" number="49792" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>any categories of non-quantitative criteria considered, which may include but need not be limited to, facility replacements, grade expansion and truncation, school rezonings, co-locating schools, and converting space in existing facilities; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38944" number="49793" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>the following information, reported at the community school district level, if utilized: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38945" number="49794" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>enrollment projections and related confidence intervals; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38946" number="49795" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>information about projected new housing; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38947" number="49796" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>any formula used for measuring capacity including class size goals; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38948" number="49797" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(4)<TAB tab-count="1"/>any relevant standards required for instructional space; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38949" number="49798" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(5)<TAB tab-count="1"/>any data used for determining a projected public school ratio; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38950" number="49799" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(6)<TAB tab-count="1"/>any new capacity projects expected to be initiated during the plan period; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38951" number="49800" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>2.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The identified seat need; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38952" number="49801" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>3.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The number of seats lost, including through lost leases; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38953" number="49802" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>4.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The number of seats gained, including through leases. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38954" number="49803" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>c.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The data provided in paragraph 2 of subdivision b of this section shall be listed for grade level kindergarten through 12 in total for the city school district and, if identified seat need is determined in such manner, shall also be listed by: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38955" number="49804" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>1.<TAB tab-count="1"/>grade level nine through 12, disaggregated by borough; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38956" number="49805" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>2.<TAB tab-count="1"/>grade level kindergarten through eight, disaggregated by community school district and subdistrict; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38957" number="49806" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>3.<TAB tab-count="1"/>grade level six through eight, disaggregated by community school district and subdistrict; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38958" number="49807" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>4.<TAB tab-count="1"/>grade level kindergarten through five, disaggregated by community school district and subdistrict. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38959" number="49808" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>d.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The data provided in paragraphs 3 and 4 of subdivision b of this section shall be listed for grade level kindergarten through 12 in total for the city school district, and shall also be listed by: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38960" number="49809" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>1.<TAB tab-count="1"/>grade level nine through 12, disaggregated by borough; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38961" number="49810" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>2.<TAB tab-count="1"/>grade level kindergarten through eight, disaggregated by community school district and subdistrict; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38962" number="49811" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>3.<TAB tab-count="1"/>grade level six through eight, disaggregated by community school district and subdistrict; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38963" number="49812" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>4.<TAB tab-count="1"/>grade level kindergarten through five, disaggregated by community school district and subdistrict. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38964" number="49813" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>e.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The data provided in paragraphs 2, 3 and 4 of subdivision b of this section shall be listed for prekindergarten programs in total for the city school district and, if available, by community school district. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38965" number="49814" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>f.<TAB tab-count="1"/>All data provided pursuant to this section shall be provided in machine readable format. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-38966" number="49815" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>g.<TAB tab-count="1"/>Nothing in this section shall be construed to affect the authority or materially impede the ability of the department to determine the identified seat need or the methodology or information utilized in the determination of identified seat need. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
